<% wrap_layout :layout do %>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 col-content">
            <div class="container container-narrow content">
                <%= yield %>
            </div>
        </div>

        <% (1..2).each do %>
        <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-2 col-sidebar">
            <div class="widget">
                <h2 class="widget-heading">Popular Posts<h2>
                <h3 class="widget-subheading">Site Speed, Web App Complexity, and Other Quanderies</h3>
                <p>When an actual backend is required, I accompany Middleman with a BaaS solution like Firebase.</p>

                <h3 class="widget-subheading">Port of the Bootstrap and Foundation Components to Inuit.css</h3>
                If all the batteries are included (but optional), there’s no reason not to use the BEM / OOCSS / SMACSS goodness of Inuit.</p>

                <h3 class="widget-subheading">Use Rails Dammit</h3>
                <p>Leaning on third party services is too rigid. If I want something as simple as password reset funtionality, I’m shit outta luck.</p>

                <h3 class="widget-subheading">Avoid Wheel-Reinventing</h3>
                <p>Rails gives me a nice DSL for building web apps, and does lots of heavy lifting without being pushy.</p>

                <h3 class="widget-subheading">Vim vs. Emacs is Like Chrome vs. Firefox</h3>
                <p>I prefer the better text editor over the more extendible one. And how about that emacs learning curve?</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <% end %>

    </div>

<% end %>